Usage: editAdjust [-help] [-adjust_size] -refer_obj {top bottom left right} {[-align_edge {left center right top middle bottom diag45_top diag45_middle diag45_bottom diag135_top diag135_middle diag135_bottom}]  [-space_mode {horizontal vertical dist_horizontal dist_vertical diag45 diag135 dist_diag45 dist_diag135} [-space <float>]]}

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-adjust_size                           # Specifies whether to adjust size of
                                       # objects. (bool, optional)
-align_edge {left center right top middle bottom diag45_top diag45_middle diag45_bottom diag135_top diag135_middle diag135_bottom}
                                       # Specifies the side of edge of wires to
                                       # align. (enum, optional)
-refer_obj {top bottom left right}     # Specifies the obj of refer when align.
                                       # (enum, required)
-space <float>                         # Specifies the space for space_mode.
                                       # (float, optional)
-space_mode {horizontal vertical dist_horizontal dist_vertical diag45 diag135 dist_diag45 dist_diag135}
                                       # Specifies whether work on space mode. (enum, optional)